(fifthQuint)Study of Nivolumab in Combination With GM.

CD40L Vaccine in Adenocarcinoma of the Lung.

 This study has two parts and participants may be involved in either Phase I part or Phase II.

 Phase I: Investigators plan to enroll participants in cohorts of 6 and monitor side effects over a 21 day period to determine the maximum tolerated dose (MTD) of nivolumab, which will be given in combination with GM.

CD40L.

 This is being done since this study involves a combination of treatments that have not been studied in humans before and to find the best dose for the Phase II part of the study.

 Phase II: Investigators plan to compare any clinical benefit in the participants who receive the combination of GM.

CD40L vaccine with nivolumab, to participants that receive only nivolumab.

